frontation and the hurdles faced by champions of tradition.The author identifies and analyzes the many areas of sociological and religious tension that divided the competing factions, including synagogue innovation, circumcision, intermarriage, military service and many others. With compelling writing and clear, articulate style, this illuminating work provides keen insight into the history and development of the various streams of Judaism and the issues that continue to divide them in contemporary times.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aJudaismy19th century. 0aJudaismy20th century. 0aOrthodox JudaismxRelationsxNontraditional Jews. 0aOrthodox Judaism. 0aReform Judaism. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / History.2bisacsh  aAlternative Rituals.  aAnti-Semitism in the Army.  aCircumcision.  aCivil Marriage.  aDenominational Press.  aFaith in an Age of Doubt.  aFeminism.  aGovernmental Intervention in Religious Practice.  aHistory.  aIntermarriage.  aJewish Denominations.  aJewish Emancipation.  aJewish Military Battalions.  aLiturgical Innovation.  aLiturgy.  aMusical Instruments and the Synagogue.  aOrthodox Periodicals.  aPacifism.  aPrayer.  aRabbinic Personalities.  aReform Judaism.  aReligious Innovation.  aSalon Society.  aSynagogue Decorum.  aSynagogue Music.  aThe Language of Prayer.  aWomen and Prayer.  aZionism and Anti-Zionism.  amodern religious practice.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068820708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZ